      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ONE MORE BUTTON (4) had been racing well prior to his last start fourth at Warrnambool following a Grade 4/5 win three back with a third placing. Meets a moderate line up and rates on top this time. GUS LIMES (2) settled off speed and overcame a chequered run to work home into the placings when third (17.75) at this track in a Grade 3/4/5. With a good start should be able to take advantage of the low draw. Harder here but expected to measure up. REVITALISE (1) was checked in the run and safely held when eighth (20.90) in a Grade 3/4/5 over 305m at this track. With a good start should be able to take advantage of the rails draw. May be worth another try. TRIAL KING (3) is worth some thought after a surprise placing last start.",
